--- xochitla2006 <xochitla2006@...> wrote:

> Hydras:
> 
> I'm thinking how rescue him... Perhaps, my scientist could interfere 
> with their base's computer but by now he doesnt get anything I'm 
> open to suggestions

Myrmidon frowned from within the dark shadows of his face mask, purple
optics glowed from deep within as he regarded Hydras. "I do not know
your team Mighty Leader, thier capabilities, thier specialties or even
thier weaknesses. Also I do not know the capabilities of our enemies or
even thier number." Myrmidon looked around as if by sheer force of will
he could pierce the layers of metal and stone and see all those things
he just mentioned; his silent thought punctuated by his clawed hands
clenching and unclenching as if fighting some internal battle.

Finally he turned back to Hydras, "I would ... suggest calling your
team together, assign one to recon the area that your subject is held -
I believe I may be the best in that area - note the enemy's weaknesses
and exploit what you can with the strengths that our team possesses."

Preston
(Myrmidon)
